name: guam-community-coral-reef-monitoring-program-macroinvertebrate-surveys-in-guam-in-2013
notes: Guam community members gathered macroinvertebrate within a 25-meter x 2-meter belt transect. Members identified macroinvertebrates to species (when possible), including echinoderms, mollusks, and crustaceans. Data is supported by photos from the sites. Surveys record total number of macroinvertebrates per 50 square meters for each transect.
